<li id="cite_note-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>Homecomers</i> were either German civilians who had been deported into the Soviet Union from those territories it conquered, or former <a href="/wiki/Wehrmacht" title="Wehrmacht">Wehrmacht</a> soldiers and <a href="/wiki/SS" title="SS" class="mw-redirect">SS</a> fighters, whom the Soviet Union caught as prisoners of war. They worked for many years as forced labourers in the Soviet Union, before they were finally released.</span></li>
